<plot>Adir, a seventeen year old fanatic director from Israel, receives an official letter from the army telling him that he is about to be recruited by the armored corps of the Israeli defense force. For Adir movies are his life, but he has another plan - he will film his masterpiece 'Arthur the IV' in order to prove to the army that he has much more talent than the ordinary tank soldier. As we follow Adir, who insists on doing all of the filming process on his own: filming, directing, acting and composing, we encounter his beautiful and naive world.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?023622</url></doc>
